25|$|Democratic Muslims is a {{political}} organization in Denmark founded by Naser Khader, Yildiz Akdogan and other Muslims in February 2006 after <b>the</b> <b>escalation</b> <b>of</b> the Jyllands-Posten Muhammad cartoons controversy. Its goal is a peaceful co-existence of Islam and democracy. Naser Khader left his position as leader in 2007. In 2009 and 2011, {{it was reported that}} the organization had few members and little activity.|$|E
