25|$|During the 1905 Revolution, Päts {{was already}} an activist on {{self-government}} reform, where he supported national autonomy in the Baltic governorates. In <b>the</b> <b>escalation</b> <b>of</b> the revolution, his newspaper {{was closed and}} its staff members arrested. Päts found out about this in advance and managed to escape to Switzerland, {{only to find out}} that he had been condemned to death in the Russian Empire.|$|E
